## Next step

Phase 8 — Frontend (5 pages: Dashboard, Patterns, Coach, Spend Check, Invest)

## Phase 7 API routes

| Method | Path | Auth | Purpose |
|--------|------|------|---------|
| GET | `/` | — | Health |
| POST | `/analyze` | optional | CSV/PDF upload (file only) → full pipeline JSON + AI goal recommendation; persists if Bearer token |
| GET | `/dashboard` | required | Latest snapshot + streak + budgets + goal recommendation from Supabase |
| GET | `/invest` | required | Invest summary + forecast + goal |
| POST | `/goal` | required | Set/update savings goal (amount, date, age) → recomputes forecast + invest |
| POST | `/spend-check` | required | Green/yellow/red purchase verdict |
| POST | `/coach` | required | AI chat with financial context |
| GET | `/coach/history` | required | Chat history |

Schema reference: `project-plan/supabase_schema.sql`

## Completed pipeline (Phases 3–7)

```text
POST /analyze → run_full_pipeline (parse → process → categorise → bills → forecast → analyze → budgets → invest → personality → snapshot)
  → optional db.persist_analysis (transactions, snapshots, streaks, goals, budgets)
```

Training data: `data/training_merchants.csv` (31 rows). Test data: `data/sample_transactions.csv`.

## Stack

Python, FastAPI, pandas, scikit-learn, Supabase, OpenAI API (optional fallbacks required), deploy Railway + Vercel.

## Conventions

- Always use `venv`; run modules as `python -m modules.<name>` from project root
- Never commit `.env`
- Bank-agnostic CSV **and text-based PDF** → normalized columns via `bank_parser.parse_bank_csv(path)` (PDFs handled by `modules/pdf_parser.py`)
- 7 categories in `config.CATEGORIES` (Food & Dining, Groceries, Transport, Subscriptions, Shopping, Health, Other)
- Income: `amount > 0` / `is_expense=False` — not ML-categorised
- Test each module on `data/sample_transactions.csv` before moving on
- Financial copy must include: "General information only, not financial advice"
- AUD, AU bank CSVs, ASX ETFs (VGS, A200, NDQ)

## Module layout

Logic lives in `modules/`. Constants and paths in `config.py`. Plan/docs in `project-plan/`.
